{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review — criterion T1 (prior-art / novel-architecture justification) for plan **B5: Cut the claim/close gates over to the workflow path (signing intact)**.\n\n**Result: PASS — no findings.**\n\nBoth bright-lines that fire here (a *migration*, and a *security/signing* surface) are well-grounded in prior art and reuse an existing substrate, so T1 is satisfied:\n\nAffirmations:\n- **T1(a) prior art considered, not reinventing.** The plan is an explicit decomposition story (B5) of epic `peak-fir-hilt`, building on B2/B3/B4. ADR 0003 (`docs/adr/0003-workflow-as-gate.md`, Status: Accepted) already establishes the \"workflow-as-gate\" pattern and names B5 verbatim as \"the epic's later cutover story\" that \"adds the gate-side helper\" + signing. The plan converges onto the *already-built* engine workflow path (`src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_ops.py`, `gates/completion-verification.yaml`, the parity scaffolding) rather than inventing a new orchestration mechanism — anti-fragmentation, not a novel architecture.\n- **T1(b) novelty justified vs. established approach (anti-repackaging / Rule-of-Three).** No novel pattern is introduced by B5; the workflow-as-gate shape is the established, reused contract (ADR 0003 \"Reused by B2\"): B3 walked the skeleton, B2 followed for plan-review, B5 cuts over. The bespoke orchestrator + direct-agent path is being *retired onto one substrate*, which is convergence, not repackaging.\n- **T1(c) capability assertions resolved.** The load-bearing claim — that the gates can dispatch through the engine workflow path with byte-compatible signing — is verifiable from the tree: the workflow path exists (`gate_ops.py` thin adapters over `rebar.llm.completion`), the signing surface the plan commits to preserve is the existing `signing.py` (canonical `(ticket_id, manifest)` HMAC payload + `key_id` fingerprint + manifest prefixes), and ADR 0003 explicitly defers signing to this cutover (\"The workflow does not sign … Cutover + signing is the epic's later cutover story (B5)\"). No unverified \"library supports X\" assertion is left dangling.\n\nNo coaching checklist items for T1."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782497538779089001,"uuid":"b672b63e-2890-4694-9038-223974ed6ac1"}